	(2119,133,'content_panels_2_content_panels_text','<p class=\"normal\">Career Navigator is based on a powerful algorithm that utilises over 25 years of research and experience from Harrison Assessments International. Harrisons have been studying the Suitability and Job Success Factors in order to map the main tasks performed and the success achieved in over 650 careers. Our research demonstrates that you are three times more likely to be successful in a career if you enjoy over 75% of the main tasks commonly required to be performed. Enjoyment Performance Theory, one of the key bases of Career Navigator, can be simply summarised to things you enjoy doing, you do more often. As you do them more often, you consequently get better at them. Makes sense doesnt it? To find out more about the psychometric theory behind Career Navigator click below.</p>'),
