	(270,1,'2015-11-06 13:51:28','2015-11-06 02:51:28','<h2>How long does it take?\nThe Career Navigator questionnaire takes approximately 20 to 30 minutes to complete and is best completed in a quiet place where you can concentrate without distraction. If for some reason you cannot complete the questionnaire, You can come back and review your reports at any time.\nDo I need to prepare?\nThere are no right or wrong answers, and you are not being ranked on your intelligence or mathematical ability. We are simply using an advanced process to match your unique combination of personality traits, interests and workplace preferences with careers where the most common tasks required are those that you will enjoy doing.\nThe bulk of the questionnaire is spent ranking statements through a drag and drop process to reflect your Suitability for over 650 Career Options.\nWhat happens next?\nOn completing the questionnaire you will be taken to the Summary page from which you can purchase Career Navigator reports. These reports include:\n  Your Greatest Strengths  what are your best traits in the workplace. Great for cv preparation\n  Career Options  provides a ranked list of suitable careers that you will enjoy\n  Career Development  what are your current strengths and weaknesses in the workplace\n  Career Enjoyment  matches you against a specific career to provided a detailed view of     what tasks you will and will not enjoy.\n  Paradox Graphs  deep insight into dynamic personality traits and communication styles in    the workplace.</h2>','What to expect','','inherit','closed','closed','','141-autosave-v1','','','2015-11-06 13:51:28','2015-11-06 02:51:28','',141,'http://forsee.com.au/141-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
