	(2027,1,'2016-01-12 11:30:00','2016-01-12 00:30:00','<h2 class=\"normal\">Our Vision</h2>\r\n<p class=\"normal\">Our vision is to change the way people go about choosing their careers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"normal\">Our aim is to be a small part of helping to create a society where people truly enjoy their jobs. A world where people are good at their work and consequently, a lot more productive. Where people are excited to wake up on Monday morning ready to embrace the challenges the working day has ahead.</p>\r\n<p class=\"normal\">When we take a step back and consider how much of our life we spend working it becomes apparent how massively important it is to our overall happiness and relationships that our careers are a match for what we like doing. Enjoy Performance Theory quite simply states that the tasks we enjoy doing, we perform more often and consequently we get better at them. For me it seems obvious that we all need to take more care in ensuring that our career choices align with this common sense concept. A healthier, happier world awaits if we get it right.</p>\r\n<p class=\"normal\">I hope you get great insights from Career Navigator and feel free to share your stories and experiences with our team.</p>\r\n<p class=\"normal\">Andrew Hartland\r\nManaging Director</p>','About Us','','inherit','closed','closed','','152-revision-v1','','','2016-01-12 11:30:00','2016-01-12 00:30:00','',152,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/152-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(2028,1,'2016-01-12 11:32:12','2016-01-12 00:32:12','<h2 class=\"normal\">Powered by Harrison Assessments</h2>\r\n<p class=\"normal\">The Career Navigators cutting edge psychometric technology is powered by Harrison Assessments who have been continuously researching, developing and finetuning workplace solutions for over 25 years.</p>\r\n<p class=\"normal\">Harrisons well established credentials in organisational psychology and applied mathematics provide the backbone of the Career Navigator solution.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"normal\">Easy to use</h2>\r\n<p class=\"normal\">The ranking of statements through the drag and drop interface is supported by a complex algorithm meaning that our 20 minute questionnaire is the equivalent of over 2,500 multiple choice questions (or a whole day).</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"normal\">Psychological Theory</h2>\r\n<p class=\"normal\">Career Navigator is based on two psychological pillars:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"normal\">Performance Enjoyment Theory - in essence what you enjoy doing, you tend to repeat and consequently get better at.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"normal\">Paradox Theory - opposite or paradoxical personality traits can combine to form positive or negative behavioural attributes which dynamically change depending on the environment or people or stress factors.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"normal\">Scientific Factors/Psych references\r\nQuote from Steven Booker?</p>','How does it work','','inherit','closed','closed','','138-revision-v1','','','2016-01-12 11:32:12','2016-01-12 00:32:12','',138,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/138-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
