VALUES
	(3335,0,'2016-01-13 11:25:45','2016-01-13 00:25:45','<p>Initiating contact via telephone with prospects who do not already have an interest in the product or service. Attempt to persuade the prospect to purchase.</p>\n','Telemarketer','','publish','closed','closed','','telemarketer','','','2016-01-13 11:25:45','2016-01-13 00:25:45','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/telemarketer/',75,'career_desc','',0),
	(3336,0,'2016-01-13 11:25:47','2016-01-13 00:25:47','<p>Develop and test models of alternate designs and processing methods to assess feasibility, operating condition effects, possible new applications and necessity of modification. Research and analyze customer design proposals, specifications, manuals or other data, to evaluate the feasibility, cost or maintenance requirements of designs or applications. Develop, improve or customize products, equipment, formulas, processes or analytical methods. Confer with scientists or engineers to conduct analyses of research projects, interpret test results or develop nonstandard tests. Direct, coordinate or advise personnel in test procedures for analysing components or physical properties of materials.</p>\n','Textile Chemistry Engineer','','publish','closed','closed','','textile-chemistry-engineer','','','2016-01-13 11:25:47','2016-01-13 00:25:47','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/textile-chemistry-engineer/',56,'career_desc','',0),
	(3337,0,'2016-01-13 11:25:49','2016-01-13 00:25:49','<p>Mix the chemical recipe for dyeing both natural and synthetic textiles. Use computer-controlled instruments to mix dyes. Decide on the chemical formula that would create the right colour. Work out the right dyeing method and temperature for the fabric. Produce the final formula for use in the manufacturing process. Recommend any special finishes or treatments to be applied after the dyeing process.</p>\n','Textile Dyeing and Finishing Technician','','publish','closed','closed','','textile-dyeing-and-finishing-technician','','','2016-01-13 11:25:49','2016-01-13 00:25:49','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/textile-dyeing-and-finishing-technician/',57,'career_desc','',0),
	(3338,0,'2016-01-13 11:25:51','2016-01-13 00:25:51','<p>Operate or tend textile machines that perform textile processing and manufacturing operations, such as winding, twisting, knitting, weaving and cutting. Start machine and observe operation to detect malfunctions or defects, such as breaking or twisting of material or thread. Examine and inspect cut yarn, lace or other material for defects, dirt and conformance to colour and size specifications. Record production information, such as lot or style number, yardage, number of defects and machine stops, and types of defects.</p>\n','Textile Machine Operator','','publish','closed','closed','','textile-machine-operator','','','2016-01-13 11:25:51','2016-01-13 00:25:51','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/textile-machine-operator/',58,'career_desc','',0),
	(3339,0,'2016-01-13 11:25:53','2016-01-13 00:25:53','<p>Perform standardized tests to determine chemical characteristics of fibre, such as shrinkage, absorbency, colour value, fading or fire retardancy. Photograph, develop and print samples of fibres, using micro photographic and photographic equipment, examine photographs or samples under microscope to determine its characteristics. Select dyes and develop colour formulas and colour charts to match textile product to customer specifications. Inspect finished material for conformance to plant and customer specifications.</p>\n','Textile Science Technician','','publish','closed','closed','','textile-science-technician','','','2016-01-13 11:25:53','2016-01-13 00:25:53','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/textile-science-technician/',59,'career_desc','',0),
	(3340,0,'2016-01-13 11:25:55','2016-01-13 00:25:55','<p>Design and test for thermal flux noise. Analyse electronic products heat dissipation structures. Conduct technical discussions with foreign and domestic customers. Carry out testing, simulations. Design and apply for heat dissipation patents.</p>\n','Thermal Engineer','','publish','closed','closed','','thermal-engineer','','','2016-01-13 11:25:55','2016-01-13 00:25:55','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/thermal-engineer/',74,'career_desc','',0),
	(3341,0,'2016-01-13 11:25:57','2016-01-13 00:25:57','<p>Apply hard tile to walls, floors, ceilings and roof decks. Cut and shape tile to fit around obstacles and into odd spaces and corners, using hand and power cutting tools. Lay and set mosaic tiles to create decorative wall, mural and floor designs. Finish and dress the joints and wipe excess grout from between tiles.</p>\n','Tile Installation Specialist','','publish','closed','closed','','tile-installation-specialist','','','2016-01-13 11:25:57','2016-01-13 00:25:57','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/tile-installation-specialist/',90,'career_desc','',0),
	(3342,0,'2016-01-13 11:25:59','2016-01-13 00:25:59','<p>Start conveyor and turn valves, controls and levers to remove bark and dirt from logs. Sort logs according to species, size and owner\'s markings into designated storage areas, using pike pole. Bind logs with chain or cable and bore holes into side and cross poles to thread chain and assemble logs into rafts for towing to mill. Guide, roll, or lift logs or log blocks onto skids, conveyors or log-haul chain for further processing. Measure and mark cutting locations on trees to obtain maximum yield of standard lengths.</p>\n','Timber Worker','','publish','closed','closed','','timber-worker','','','2016-01-13 11:25:59','2016-01-13 00:25:59','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/timber-worker/',91,'career_desc','',0),
	(3343,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:00','2016-01-13 00:26:00','<p>Repair and replace tires, tubes, treads and related products on automobiles, buses, trucks and other vehicles. Remove wheel from vehicle by hand or by use of power hoist, and locate puncture in tire by visual inspection or by immersing inflated tire in water bath and observing air bubbles. Seal puncture in tire by inserting adhesive material and expanding rubber plug into puncture, using hand tools. Remount wheel onto vehicle.</p>\n','Tyre Fitting and Repair Specialist','','publish','closed','closed','','tyre-fitting-and-repair-specialist','','','2016-01-13 11:26:00','2016-01-13 00:26:00','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/tyre-fitting-and-repair-specialist/',92,'career_desc','',0),
	(3344,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:02','2016-01-13 00:26:02','<p>Search lot books, geographic and general indices, and assessor\'s rolls, to compile lists of transactions pertaining to property. Read search request to ascertain type of title evidence required, and to obtain description of property and names of involved parties. Compare legal description of property with legal description contained in records and indices, to verify such factors as deed ownership. Confer with realtors, lending institution personnel, buyers, sellers, contractors, surveyors and courthouse personnel to obtain additional information. Prepare title commitment and final policy of title insurance, based on information compiled from title search, as well as closing statement, utilizing knowledge and expertise in real estate procedures.</p>\n','Conveyancer','','publish','closed','closed','','conveyancer','','','2016-01-13 11:26:02','2016-01-13 00:26:02','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/conveyancer/',93,'career_desc','',0),
	(3345,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:04','2016-01-13 00:26:04','<p>Escort groups on establishment tours, describes points of interest, and respond to questions. Drive motor vehicle to transport visitors to establishments and tour site locations, and provide directions and other pertinent information to visitors. Monitor visitors\' activities and ensure compliance with establishment regulations, for safety of group. Solicit tour patronage and collect fees and tickets from group members.</p>\n','Tour Guide','','publish','closed','closed','','tour-guide','','','2016-01-13 11:26:04','2016-01-13 00:26:04','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/tour-guide/',94,'career_desc','',0),
	(3346,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:06','2016-01-13 00:26:06','<p>Research effects of toxic substances on physiological functions of humans, animals and plants, for consumer protection and industrial safety programs. Design and conduct studies to determine physiological effects of various substances on laboratory animals, plants and human tissue. Interpret results of studies in terms of toxicological properties of substances and hazards associated with their misuse. Write and maintain records and reports of studies and tests, for use as toxicological resource material. Advise governmental and industrial personnel on degree of hazard of toxic materials and on precautionary labelling.</p>\n','Toxicologist','','publish','closed','closed','','toxicologist','','','2016-01-13 11:26:06','2016-01-13 00:26:06','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/toxicologist/',96,'career_desc','',0),
	(3347,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:08','2016-01-13 00:26:08','<p>Analyse physical findings and medical histories to make diagnoses according to Oriental medicine traditions. Treat patients using tools such as needles, cups, herb diet, exercise and lifestyle adjustments. Develop individual treatment plans and strategies. Evaluate treatment outcomes and recommend new or altered treatments as necessary to promote health.</p>\n','Traditional Chinese Medicine Practitioner','','publish','closed','closed','','traditional-chinese-medicine-practitioner','','','2016-01-13 11:26:08','2016-01-13 00:26:08','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/traditional-chinese-medicine-practitioner/',97,'career_desc','',0),
	(3348,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:10','2016-01-13 00:26:10','<p>Install, inspect, test, maintain or repair electric gate crossings, signals, signal equipment, track switches, section lines or intercommunications systems within a railroad system. Inspect and test operation, mechanical parts and circuitry of gate crossings, signals and signal equipment, such as interlocks and hotbox detectors. Install, inspect, maintain and repair various railroad service equipment on the road or in the shop, including railroad signal systems. Record and report information about mileage or track inspected, repairs performed and equipment requiring replacement.</p>\n','Railway Signalling Technician','','publish','closed','closed','','railway-signalling-technician','','','2016-01-13 11:26:10','2016-01-13 00:26:10','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/railway-signalling-technician/',98,'career_desc','',0),
	(3349,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:12','2016-01-13 00:26:12','<p>Perform scheduled maintenance, and clean units and components. Inspect the interior and exterior of trains coming into rail yards in order to identify defects and to determine the extent of wear and damage. Repair or replace defective or worn parts such as bearings, pistons and gears, using hand tools, torque wrenches, power tools and welding equipment. Test units for operability before and after repairs.</p>\n','Locomotive Maintenance Mechanic','','publish','closed','closed','','locomotive-maintenance-mechanic','','','2016-01-13 11:26:12','2016-01-13 00:26:12','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/locomotive-maintenance-mechanic/',99,'career_desc','',0),
	(3350,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:14','2016-01-13 00:26:14','<p>Analyse a subject and develop high quality training materials using software applications.</p>\n','Training Materials Developer','','publish','closed','closed','','training-materials-developer','','','2016-01-13 11:26:14','2016-01-13 00:26:14','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/training-materials-developer/',95,'career_desc','',0),
	(3351,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:16','2016-01-13 00:26:16','<p>Identify the aims of the training to ensure the training fulfils the purpose. Organize and conduct training. Obtain feedback and improve the training delivery and/or content.</p>\n','Training Specialist','','publish','closed','closed','','training-specialist','','','2016-01-13 11:26:16','2016-01-13 00:26:16','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/training-specialist/',100,'career_desc','',0),
	(3352,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:18','2016-01-13 00:26:18','<p>Operate and maintain radio transmitter to broadcast radio and television programs. Monitor console panel and signal emission and make adjustments as needed to maintain quality of transmission. Test components of malfunctioning transmitter to diagnose trouble, using test equipment, such as oscilloscope, voltmeters, and ammeters. Converse with studio personnel to determine cause of equipment failure and to solve problem.</p>\n','Transmitter Engineer','','publish','closed','closed','','transmitter-engineer','','','2016-01-13 11:26:18','2016-01-13 00:26:18','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/transmitter-engineer/',101,'career_desc','',0),
	(3353,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:20','2016-01-13 00:26:20','<p>Assist medical team in retrieval of organs for transplantation, using medical instruments. Solicit medical and community groups for organ donors. Communicate with donors, patients and health team members to ensure comprehensive documentation. Analyse medical data of organ donors and recipients from medical and social records, physical examination and consultation with health team. Correlate and summarize laboratory reports, X-rays and office test to assist physician to determine medical suitability or procedure. Advise post-operative patients on therapies for managing health after transplant, and serve as team member monitor.</p>\n','Transplant Coordinator','','publish','closed','closed','','transplant-coordinator','','','2016-01-13 11:26:20','2016-01-13 00:26:20','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/transplant-coordinator/',89,'career_desc','',0),
	(3354,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:22','2016-01-13 00:26:22','<p>Operate or tend painting machines to paint surfaces of transportation equipment, such as automobiles, buses, trucks, boats and airplanes. Paint designs, letterings or identifying information on vehicles. Select paint according to company requirements and matches colours of paint following specified colour charts. Operate lifting and moving devices to move equipment or materials to access areas to be painted.</p>\n','Transportation Equipment Painter','','publish','closed','closed','','transportation-equipment-painter','','','2016-01-13 11:26:22','2016-01-13 00:26:22','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/transportation-equipment-painter/',88,'career_desc','',0),
	(3355,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:23','2016-01-13 00:26:23','<p>Plan, describe, arrange and sell itinerary tour packages and promotional travel incentives, offered by various travel carriers. Converse with customer to determine destination, mode of transportation, travel dates, financial considerations, and accommodations required. Compute cost of travel and accommodations, using calculator, computer, carrier tariff books and hotel rate books, or quote package tour costs, and books transportation and hotel reservations. Collect payment for transportation and accommodations from customer.</p>\n','Travel Agent','','publish','closed','closed','','travel-agent','','','2016-01-13 11:26:23','2016-01-13 00:26:23','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/travel-agent/',76,'career_desc','',0),
	(3356,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:25','2016-01-13 00:26:25','<p>Drive truck to transport and deliver cargo, materials or damaged vehicle. Maintain radio or telephone contact with base or supervisor to receive instructions or be dispatched to new location. Keep record of materials and products transported. Position blocks and ties rope around items to secure cargo for transport. Operate equipment on vehicle to load, unload or disperse cargo or materials.</p>\n','Truck Driver','','publish','closed','closed','','truck-driver','','','2016-01-13 11:26:25','2016-01-13 00:26:25','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/truck-driver/',77,'career_desc','',0),
	(3357,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:27','2016-01-13 00:26:27','<p>Determine eligibility of persons applying to receive assistance from government programs and agency resources for unemployment benefits, by interviewing claimants. Initiate procedures to grant, modify, deny, or terminate assistance or refer applicants to other agencies for assistance. Compile, record, and evaluate personal and financial data in order to verify completeness and accuracy and to determine eligibility status. Check with employers or other references to verify answers and obtain further information.</p>\n','Job Seeker Benefits Officer','','publish','closed','closed','','job-seeker-benefits-officer','','','2016-01-13 11:26:27','2016-01-13 00:26:27','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/job-seeker-benefits-officer/',78,'career_desc','',0),
	(3358,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:29','2016-01-13 00:26:29','<p>Plan, administer and control budgets, maintain financial records and produce financial reports at postsecondary institutions, such as colleges or universities. Establish operational policies and procedures and make any necessary changes. Formulate strategic plans. Participate in student recruitment, selection and admissions. Advise, counsel and discipline students. Recruit, hire, train, terminate departmental personnel.</p>\n','University Administrator','','publish','closed','closed','','university-administrator','','','2016-01-13 11:26:29','2016-01-13 00:26:29','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/university-administrator/',79,'career_desc','',0),
	(3359,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:31','2016-01-13 00:26:31','<p>Teach university students in Agricultural Science. Prepare instructional materials and adapt teaching methods to meet students\' varying needs and interests. Establish clear objectives for all lessons, units and projects, and communicate these objectives to students.</p>\n','University Agricultural Science Lecturer','','publish','closed','closed','','university-agricultural-science-lecturer','','','2016-01-13 11:26:31','2016-01-13 00:26:31','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/university-agricultural-science-lecturer/',80,'career_desc','',0),
	(3360,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:33','2016-01-13 00:26:33','<p>Teach courses in the arts including fine and applied art, such as painting and sculpture, or design and crafts. Explain and demonstrate artistic techniques. Evaluate and grade students\' class work, performances, projects, assignments and papers. Prepare and periodically revise course materials, such as syllabi, homework assignments and handouts.</p>\n','University Art Lecturer','','publish','closed','closed','','university-art-lecturer','','','2016-01-13 11:26:33','2016-01-13 00:26:33','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/university-art-lecturer/',81,'career_desc','',0),
	(3361,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:35','2016-01-13 00:26:35','<p>Teach courses pertaining to business, such as business, marketing or accounting. Prepare course materials, such as syllabi, homework assignments and handouts. Prepare and deliver lectures to undergraduate or graduate students. Evaluate and grade students\' class work, laboratory work, assignments, and papers. Supervise undergraduate or graduate teaching, internship and research work.</p>\n','University Business Related Subject Lecturer','','publish','closed','closed','','university-business-related-subject-lecturer','','','2016-01-13 11:26:35','2016-01-13 00:26:35','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/university-business-related-subject-lecturer/',82,'career_desc','',0),
	(3362,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:37','2016-01-13 00:26:37','<p>Teach courses pertaining to the chemical and physical properties and compositional changes of substances. Prepare course materials, such as syllabi, homework assignments and handouts. Prepare and deliver lectures. Evaluate and grade students\' class work and examinations, laboratory performance, assignments and papers. Supervise students\' laboratory work.</p>\n','University Chemistry Lecturer','','publish','closed','closed','','university-chemistry-lecturer','','','2016-01-13 11:26:37','2016-01-13 00:26:37','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/university-chemistry-lecturer/',83,'career_desc','',0),
	(3363,0,'2016-01-13 11:26:39','2016-01-13 00:26:39','<p>Teach courses in computer science by preparing and delivering lectures to undergraduate or graduate students. Evaluate and grade students\' class work, laboratory work, assignments and papers. Prepare course materials, such as syllabi, homework assignments and handouts. Keep abreast of developments in the field by reading current literature, talking with colleagues and participating in professional conferences.</p>\n','University Computer Science Lecturer','','publish','closed','closed','','university-computer-science-lecturer','','','2016-01-13 11:26:39','2016-01-13 00:26:39','',0,'http://forsee.192.168.1.200.xip.io:8888/career_desc/university-computer-science-lecturer/',84,'career_desc','',0),
